cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

This paper compares two datasets that monitor news articles worldwide, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract and analyze news data. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may involve machine learning and deep learning techniques for data analysis, which could fall under cs.DL (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with big data and its impact on society, cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be a possible sub-category.
